<task id="025" project="sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair">
  <metadata>
    <title>Fix broken sdap-ci.yml workflow — restore Build &amp; Test (Release) signal</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>1-3 hours</estimated-effort>
    <assigned>AI agent</assigned>
    <tags>phase-1, ci-cd, workflow, p1-d, scope-absorption</tags>
    <parallel-group>1-D-post-factory</parallel-group>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <parallel-reason>Edits `.github/workflows/sdap-ci.yml` — must not run concurrent with task 018 (factory ISOLATED per NFR-07) because the same `dotnet test` outcome feeds both the factory measurement (task 019) AND this workflow run. Sequence: 018 → 019 → 025.</parallel-reason>
    <rigor>FULL</rigor>
    <repair-not-rewrite>true</repair-not-rewrite>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    Task 023 (CI gate negative-path verification) discovered that `sdap-ci.yml` is broken on
    EVERY recent run, including master. Each run completes in 0 seconds with `conclusion: failure`
    and `workflow_run_id: 0`. The required `Build &amp; Test (Release)` status check is therefore
    never POSTED — PRs fail merge with "check expected but missing" rather than a real test result.

    Master is effectively LOCKED for all merges until this is repaired. Outcome C (CI gate
    restoration) is incomplete without this fix.

    Per owner directive 2026-05-31 (absorb deviations into THIS project; do not defer): this
    task delivers the workflow repair within Phase 1 P1.D track.

    Investigate the 0-second failure (likely YAML syntax, missing secret, path filter, or
    `permissions:` gate issue). Repair `sdap-ci.yml`. Confirm via a NEW deliberate-success PR
    that `Build &amp; Test (Release)` now posts a real pass/fail signal.
  </prompt>

  <role>AI agent diagnosing GitHub Actions workflow brokenness and applying the minimum-viable repair.</role>

  <goal>
    `.github/workflows/sdap-ci.yml` runs correctly: completes successfully (or fails for a REAL
    reason — not 0s with empty conclusion), posts the named `Build &amp; Test (Release)` status
    check, and unblocks master merges. A deliberate-success PR verifies the signal.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="workflow-target">.github/workflows/sdap-ci.yml</file>
    <file purpose="task-023-evidence">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/baseline/ci-gate-verification-2026-05-31.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="design">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/design.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="NFR-01">No `src/`, `power-platform/`, `infra/`, `scripts/` changes — workflow file is in `.github/` which is editable for this project</constraint>
    <constraint source="NFR-09">`repair-not-rewrite: true` — diagnose + minimum-viable fix; do NOT redesign the workflow</constraint>
    <constraint source="D-02">Restoration must preserve `enforce_admins: true` + 3 required status checks (`Build &amp; Test (Debug)`, `Build &amp; Test (Release)`, `Code Quality`); do NOT relax branch protection to "fix" CI</constraint>
    <constraint source="§4.5">N/A (not factory work) — but follow NFR-07 spirit: sequence after Wave 1.3 (018+019) to avoid muddying the test signal</constraint>
    <constraint source="owner-2026-05-31">Mid-project discoveries absorb into this project; deferral not permitted</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/CLAUDE.md</file>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/baseline/ci-gate-verification-2026-05-31.md</file>
      <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/decisions/D-02-ci-gate-strict.md</file>
    </files>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      Task 023 produced detailed evidence at `baseline/ci-gate-verification-2026-05-31.md`
      documenting the 0-second-failure pattern. Common root causes for this pattern (in
      decreasing likelihood):

      1. YAML syntax error introduced by a recent commit (workflow doesn't load at all)
      2. Missing or expired GitHub Actions secret (e.g., `AZURE_CREDENTIALS`, deploy keys)
         — the job fails on secret-resolution before any step runs
      3. `permissions:` block too restrictive — GitHub denies workflow before launch
      4. Path filter (`on.push.paths` / `paths-ignore`) excludes everything
      5. `if:` gate on the job evaluates to false on every event
      6. Self-hosted runner labels reference a runner that doesn't exist
      7. Concurrency cancellation killing every run before steps execute

      Diagnostic order: read the workflow file, then check the most recent failed runs via
      `gh run list --workflow=sdap-ci.yml --limit 5 --json status,conclusion,startedAt,headBranch,event`
      and `gh run view {run-id} --log` to see what (if anything) happened during execution.

      Investigation may surface that the workflow needs a substantive fix vs. a one-line patch.
      Per NFR-09 + scope: prefer the minimum-viable repair that restores the signal. If the
      fix requires &gt;50% workflow rewrite, escalate per §4.8 with
      `escalations/rewrite-request-T-025-sdap-ci.md`.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="023" status="completed">CI gate verification evidence captured; finding documented</dependency>
      <dependency task="019" status="not-started">Factory verification gate (Wave 1.3) — sequence after to avoid muddying signal</dependency>
    </dependencies>
  </context>

  <relevant-files>
    <file>.github/workflows/sdap-ci.yml</file>
    <file>projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/baseline/sdap-ci-repair-evidence-2026-05-31.md</file>
  </relevant-files>

  <steps>
    <step order="1">Read current `.github/workflows/sdap-ci.yml` end-to-end. Note the workflow name, triggers, jobs, and the 3 status-check job names (`Build &amp; Test (Debug)`, `Build &amp; Test (Release)`, `Code Quality`).</step>

    <step order="2">Run `gh run list --workflow=sdap-ci.yml --limit 10 --json status,conclusion,startedAt,headBranch,event,databaseId` to confirm the 0s-failure pattern. Capture the last 3-5 run IDs.</step>

    <step order="3">For each captured run ID: `gh run view {run-id}` and `gh run view {run-id} --log` (full log if available; if empty, that confirms steps never executed). Look for: secret-resolution errors, YAML parse errors at workflow load, `permissions:` denials, runner-not-found errors.</step>

    <step order="4">Diagnose the root cause. Document in `projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/baseline/sdap-ci-repair-evidence-2026-05-31.md`:
      - Run IDs investigated
      - Log excerpts showing the failure mode (or noting if logs are empty)
      - Root-cause hypothesis with evidence
      - Proposed minimum-viable fix (size estimate: how many lines, which sections)
    </step>

    <step order="5">If the proposed fix is &lt;50% line replacement: apply it. If &gt;50%: HALT and file `escalations/rewrite-request-T-025-sdap-ci.md` per §4.8.</step>

    <step order="6">Validate locally: parse the modified YAML with `python -c "import yaml; yaml.safe_load(open('.github/workflows/sdap-ci.yml'))"` (works because the worktree has Python). Verify `gh workflow view sdap-ci.yml` after pushing reports no syntax errors.</step>

    <step order="7">Open a deliberate-success PR to validate the repair end-to-end:
      a. Create branch `test/sdap-ci-repair-verify-2026-05-31` from `work/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair`
      b. Push the workflow fix to that branch
      c. Open a PR with title `[CI repair verify] do not merge`
      d. Wait for the workflow to run (expected 10-25 min for full unit-test suite)
      e. Confirm `Build &amp; Test (Release)` posts a REAL pass/fail status (not "missing")
      f. Confirm the workflow completes in &gt;0 seconds with a real conclusion
    </step>

    <step order="8">Two outcome paths:
      - If the workflow now passes: the fix is good. Close the verify PR (without merging — the fix needs to land on `work/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair` via the project's normal flow, NOT via this verify branch). Delete the verify branch on remote.
      - If the workflow now FAILS (real test failure, not 0s): the fix is working — it correctly reports test state. Capture this as evidence; the test failures are Phase 2+3's problem.
    </step>

    <step order="9">Apply the workflow fix to `work/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair` (cherry-pick or re-apply the edit). The fix should be committed normally as part of this project's progression.</step>

    <step order="10">Update `current-task.md` with: workflow fix description, evidence path, verify-PR URL + outcome, deliberate-success branch cleanup status, P1.D track final exit declaration.</step>

    <step order="11">Update task 025 POML status to `completed` with completion notes.</step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="gh">CLI for run inspection + PR creation</tool>
    <tool name="Read">workflow YAML + 023 evidence</tool>
    <tool name="Edit">workflow YAML repair</tool>
    <tool name="Bash">YAML validation + git branch ops</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="workflow-fix">.github/workflows/sdap-ci.yml (repaired)</output>
    <output type="evidence">projects/sdap-bff.api-test-suite-repair/baseline/sdap-ci-repair-evidence-2026-05-31.md</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`.github/workflows/sdap-ci.yml` parses as valid YAML (`python yaml.safe_load`)</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`gh workflow view sdap-ci.yml` reports no syntax errors</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">A new deliberate-success PR (or the work/ branch's own next CI run) shows the workflow runs &gt;0 seconds AND posts the `Build &amp; Test (Release)` status check</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`baseline/sdap-ci-repair-evidence-2026-05-31.md` documents root cause + fix + verification</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">No modifications to `src/`, `power-platform/`, `infra/`, `scripts/`</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">If the repair required &gt;50% workflow rewrite, `escalations/rewrite-request-T-025-sdap-ci.md` exists</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">D-02 binding preserved: `enforce_admins: true` + 3 required status checks still in branch protection</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>

  <notes>
    <origin date="2026-05-31" source="Task 023 CI gate negative-path verification finding">
      Discovered during Wave 1.2 task 023's deliberate-fail PR test: every `sdap-ci.yml` run
      across master + all active branches completes in 0 seconds with `conclusion: failure`
      and no real status check posted. PR #312 was correctly refused merge (gate works), but
      the gate's signal is broken (every PR fails for "missing check" rather than a real test
      result). Master is operationally locked for all merges until repaired.

      Per owner directive 2026-05-31 ("absorb deviations, don't defer"), this task delivers
      the workflow repair within Phase 1 P1.D track instead of escalating to a follow-on
      project. Sequenced after Wave 1.3 (factory ISOLATED) to avoid muddying the post-factory
      test signal during task 019's measurement.
    </origin>
  </notes>
</task>
